#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.14:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.14:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 14. Daliddasutta → daḷiddasuttaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn11.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Daliddasutta"
msgstr "14. Poor"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.14:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn11.14:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn11.14:1.3"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "sn11.14:1.4"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "sn11.14:1.5"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.232"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.498"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: manussadaliddo → manussadaḷiddo (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn11.14:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, aññataro puriso imasmiṃyeva rājagahe manussadaliddo "
"ahosi manussakapaṇo manussavarāko."
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, there was a poor person, impoverished and "
"pitiful."

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.2"
msgid ""
"So tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye saddhaṃ samādiyi, sīlaṃ samādiyi, sutaṃ "
"samādiyi, cāgaṃ samādiyi, paññaṃ samādiyi."
msgstr ""
"They took up faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom in the teaching "
"and training proclaimed by the Realized One."

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.3"
msgid ""
"So tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye saddhaṃ samādiyitvā sīlaṃ samādiyitvā "
"sutaṃ samādiyitvā cāgaṃ samādiyitvā paññaṃ samādiyitvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajji devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"After undertaking these things, when their body broke up, after death, they "
"were reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, in the company of the gods of "
"the Thirty-Three."

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.4"
msgid "So aññe deve atirocati vaṇṇena ceva yasasā ca."
msgstr "There they outshone the other gods in beauty and glory."

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti:"
msgstr "But the gods of the Thirty-Three complained, grumbled, and objected:"

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.6"
msgid "‘acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "‘It’s incredible, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.7"
msgid ""
"Ayañhi devaputto pubbe manussabhūto samāno manussadaliddo ahosi "
"manussakapaṇo manussavarāko;"
msgstr ""
"For when this god was a human being in their past life they were poor, "
"impoverished, and pitiful."

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.8"
msgid ""
"so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ "
"tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"And when their body broke up, after death, they were reborn in a good place, "
"a heavenly realm, in the company of the gods of the Thirty-Three."

msgctxt "sn11.14:2.9"
msgid "So aññe deve atirocati vaṇṇena ceva yasasā cā’ti."
msgstr "Here they outshine the other gods in beauty and glory.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.14:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three:"

msgctxt "sn11.14:3.2"
msgid "‘mā kho tumhe, mārisā, etassa devaputtassa ujjhāyittha."
msgstr "‘Good sirs, don’t complain about this god."

msgctxt "sn11.14:3.3"
msgid ""
"Eso kho, mārisā, devaputto pubbe manussabhūto samāno tathāgatappavedite "
"dhammavinaye saddhaṃ samādiyi, sīlaṃ samādiyi, sutaṃ samādiyi, cāgaṃ "
"samādiyi, paññaṃ samādiyi."
msgstr ""
"When this god was a human being in their past life they took up faith, "
"ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom in the teaching and training "
"proclaimed by the Realized One."

msgctxt "sn11.14:3.4"
msgid ""
"So tathāgatappavedite dhammavinaye saddhaṃ samādiyitvā sīlaṃ samādiyitvā "
"sutaṃ samādiyitvā cāgaṃ samādiyitvā paññaṃ samādiyitvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"After undertaking these things, when their body broke up, after death, they’"
"ve been reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm, in the company of the gods "
"of the Thirty-Three."

msgctxt "sn11.14:3.5"
msgid "So aññe deve atirocati vaṇṇena ceva yasasā cā’ti."
msgstr "Here they outshine the other gods in beauty and glory.’"

msgctxt "sn11.14:3.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse anunayamāno tāyaṃ "
"velāyaṃ imā gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Sakka, lord of gods, guiding the gods of the Thirty-Three, recited this "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.499"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.14:4.1"
msgid "‘Yassa saddhā tathāgate,"
msgstr "‘Whoever has faith in the Realized One,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:4.2"
msgid "acalā suppatiṭṭhitā;"
msgstr "unwavering and well grounded;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:4.3"
msgid "Sīlañca yassa kalyāṇaṃ,"
msgstr "whose ethical conduct is good,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:4.4"
msgid "ariyakantaṃ pasaṃsitaṃ."
msgstr "praised and loved by the noble ones;"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.14:5.1"
msgid "Saṅghe pasādo yassatthi,"
msgstr "who has confidence in the Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:5.2"
msgid "ujubhūtañca dassanaṃ;"
msgstr "and correct view:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:5.3"
msgid "Adaliddoti taṃ āhu,"
msgstr "they’re said to be prosperous,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:5.4"
msgid "amoghaṃ tassa jīvitaṃ."
msgstr "their life is not in vain."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.14:6.1"
msgid "Tasmā saddhañca sīlañca,"
msgstr "So let the wise devote themselves"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:6.2"
msgid "pasādaṃ dhammadassanaṃ;"
msgstr "to faith, ethical behaviour,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:6.3"
msgid "Anuyuñjetha medhāvī,"
msgstr "confidence, and insight into the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.14:6.4"
msgid "saraṃ buddhāna sāsanan’”ti."
msgstr "remembering the instructions of the Buddhas.’”"
